Standard Portable Library

spl is a pointer friendly C/C++ STL replacement.  It uses an API similar to 
java or .net and includes network and database support.  The principles of
the debug version were reused from Steve Maguire's book, "Writing Solid
Code".

Bugs & Issues

	- See the TODO file.

Optional Requirments

	- None: support for freetds and mysql have been removed.

Installation

	./configure
	make
	make check
	make install

Quickstart

	See docs/quickstart.html

